    <updated>2024-07-29T22:21:35.006000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>gregorw</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12545</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hello Kyma Experts,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;when using the helm charts generated by CAP there is a&amp;nbsp;ServiceBinding to XSUAA which is used via a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;volume mount of the service binding&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;secretName. I would like to use this secrets also in the&amp;nbsp;APIRule for a&amp;nbsp;jwt accessStrategies configuration. In &lt;A href="https://github.com/gregorwolf/cap-azure-ad-b2c/blob/main/kyma/deployment.yaml#L49" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://github.com/gregorwolf/cap-azure-ad-b2c/blob/main/kyma/deployment.yaml#L49&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;I did this manually with a static configuration of the&amp;nbsp;trusted_issuers and&amp;nbsp;jwks_urls. But I want to get the configuration be flexible so I do not need to adjust it between dev / qa and production.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Best Regards&lt;BR /&gt;Gregor&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/use-servicebinding-data-for-apirule-jwt-accessstrategies-configuration/qaq-p/13775984"/>
    <published>2024-07-29T22:21:35.006000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
